git rgit git lls
1. Created folder.
 
2. "cd (folder name)"

3. git init

4. touch index.html
 
5. Create some basic Html in this file and save it.
 
6. Run git status and you should see something similar to this.

7. git add (filename, in this case index.html)

8. git commit -m "(whatever you want the commit message to be)"
 
9. run "git remote add origin (name of remote location - 'origin') (the url you copied from github)"

10. run "git remote -v" to see that the URL is in the list.

11. git push -u origin master

If you create a readme file you don't have to go through all this, just clone the entire repo.